    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen I start `nvim` with `nvim -u NONE` and run `:set linebreak cc=50`, I get\r\n\r\n![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16707112/258635848-c35029ea-3225-476c-b4ce-82f05bd99435.png)\r\nThis is as expected, colorcolumn is occupying the col number 50.\r\n\r\nWhen I resize the terminal so that the `linebreak` option because active and `cc` overflows to the next line, I get\r\n\r\n![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16707112/258635906-31983cef-298d-4b7d-984f-ad165d6ba0df.png)\r\nThe colorcolumn is now two characters earlier, and the \"a\" where it was originally has coordinate `1,50-52`. \"g\" has coordinate `1,48-50` and that's I guess why it was selected as colorcolumn.\r\n\r\nI didn't find anything in the docs about this behavior. Would it be possible to instead use the smallest number of the column coordinate interval such that colorcolumn is consistent w.r.t resizing? Is this a bug or a feature?\r\n\r\nSimilar problem arrises with e.g. `:set breakindent cc=50` as well as `:set showbreak=> cc=50`\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nnvim -u NONE\r\n:set linebreak cc=50\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI would expect the colorcolumn to be at the original location\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.1 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nyes, 9.0.1424 (https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/12743)\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 13.4.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\niterm2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256 color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
